    Defines a wrapper around a CoordinateCartesianAbsolute and a CoordinateWorld3D with the intent that the latter will be the target form. If the CoordinateWorld3D is provided initially, then no further action is needed. If the CoordinateCartesianAbsolute is provided, then it will need to be resolved to the CoordinateWorld3D at some point. The standard interpretation of the CoordinateCartesianAbsolute is a relative offset in feet from (0,0), where positive is up and right. The resolution process translates this relative position into an absolute world position in latitude and longitude based on a reference point in world coordinates.
